OL,5, Japanese zoologist and filmmaker       
OL,6, Masanori Hata, who made connecting     
OL,7, humans with animals his life's purpose,
OL,8, has died at 87.                        
OL,10,FMutsugoro, as he was fondly known, was 
OL,11,Ffamous for directing The Adventures of 
OL,12,FMilo and Otis, an 80s classic about the
OL,13,Funlikely friendship between a kitten   
OL,14,Fand a pug.                             
OL,16,FBack home in Japan, he also served as  
OL,17,Fan oracle of sorts for TV audiences who
OL,18,Fwanted to better understand their pets.
OL,20,FHe reportedly died of a heart attack.  
